Enum Validation.Type

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<Validation.Type>
      • com.alexandriasoftware.swing.Validation.Type
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<Validation.Type>
    Enclosing class:
    Validation
    public static enum Validation.Type
extends Enum<Validation.Type>
    The Validation state. The states DANGER and WARNING are considered invalid in JInputValidator.verify(javax.swing.JComponent) and all other states are considered valid.

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants

      DANGER

      SUCCESS

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • NONE

        public static final Validation.Type NONE
        Default state with no validation icon or tool tip displayed. If the component being validated has a default tool tip, that tool tip is displayed.

      • UNKNOWN

        public static final Validation.Type UNKNOWN
        Validation state with an unknown icon and tool tip. By default the icon is a question mark in a circle in the default border color. Considered informative and valid.

      • INFORMATION

        public static final Validation.Type INFORMATION
        Validation state with an information icon and tool tip. By default the icon is a letter I in a circle in the default border color. Considered informative and valid.

      • SUCCESS

        public static final Validation.Type SUCCESS
        Validation state with a success icon and tool tip. By default the icon is a check mark in a circle in green. Considered informative and valid.

      • WARNING

        public static final Validation.Type WARNING
        Validation state with an warning icon and tool tip. By default the icon is an exclamation mark in a triangle in yellow. Considered invalid.

      • DANGER

        public static final Validation.Type DANGER
        Validation state with an danger icon and tool tip. By default the icon is a letter X in a circle in red. Considered invalid.
